HEADWORD: Jamaicine
<hw>Ja*ma"i*cine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<ets>Jamaica</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>An alkaloid said to
be contained in the bark of <spn>Geoffroya inermis</spn>, a leguminous
tree growing in Jamaica and Surinam; -- called also
<altname>jamacina</altname>.</def> <rj><au>Watts.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
